author: COMSOL
description: The Marangoni effect produces a slip velocity in the tangential direction on a fluid/fluid interface when gradients in the surface tension coefficient are present. In this example, a long fluid jet breaks up in the inertial reference frame as a result of a periodic surface tension gradient.
label: jet_instability_mm.mph
